[[File:Android 4.0.png|thumb|200px|Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich" features the Roboto font]] '''Roboto''' is a [[Sans-serif#Classification|sans-serif typeface]] family introduced with [[Android_version_history#4.x_Ice_Cream_Sandwich|Android 4.0 "Ice Cream Sandwich"]] operating system.<ref name="Sandwich">{{cite web |url=http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2011/10/android-ice-cream-sandwich-3/ |title=Goggle's New Font |author= |date=October 19,2011 |work=Wired |publisher=Wired |accessdate=November 4, 2011}}</ref> Google describes the font as "modern, yet approachable" and "emotional".<ref name="ICE">{{cite web |title = New Design Philosophy of Ice Cream Sandwich |url = http://www.engadget.com/2011/10/18/roboto-and-the-new-design-philosophy-of-android-4-0-ice-cream-s/|work = Engadget |publisher = Engadget |accessdate = November 4,2011 }}</ref><ref name="Cream">{{cite web |title = Design of Roboto |url = http://news.in.msn.com/technology/article.aspx?cp-documentid=5526341 |work = MSN |publisher = MSN |accessdate = November 4,2011 }}</ref> ==Development== The font was designed entirely in-house at [[Google]] by Christian Robertson, an interface designer for Google, who previously had designed the [[Ubuntu (operating system) | Ubuntu]] Titling Font through his personal type foundry betatype.<ref name="Work">{{cite web |title = Association with Google and betatype |url = http://christianrobertson.com/ |work = Christian Robertson |publisher =Christian Robertson |accessdate = November 12,2011 }}</ref><ref name="Frankenfont">{{cite web |title = Roboto is a Four-headed Frankenfont |url = http://typographica.org/2011/on-typography/roboto-typeface-is-a-four-headed-frankenstein/ |work = TypoGraphica |publisher =TypoGraphica |accessdate = November 4,2011 }}</ref> ===Reception=== Reception of the font has been mixed. Joshua Topolsky, at [[The Verge]], describes the font as "clean and modern, but not overly futuristic â not a science fiction font"<ref name="Google">{{cite web |title = Font Design In-house |url = http://www.theverge.com/2011/10/18/exclusive-matias-duarte-ice-cream-sandwich-galaxy-nexus/ |work = The Verge |publisher = The Verge |accessdate = November 28,2011 }}</ref> ,while John Gruber, of [[Daring Fireball]], called it "Google's [[Arial]]" due to perceived similarities with [[Helvetica]].<ref name="Gruber">{{cite web |title = Critique |url = http://daringfireball.net/2011/10/font_hipsters |work = Daring Fireball |publisher =Daring Fireball |accessdate = November 4,2011 }}</ref> <ref name="Arial">{{cite web |title = Google's Arial |url = http://daringfireball.net/linked/2011/10/19/roboto-v-helvetica |work = Daring Fireball |publisher =Daring Fireball |accessdate = November 4,2011 }}</ref>
Stephen Coles, former Type Director at [[FontShop]], criticized the font for being an unattractive imitation of [[Helvetica]] and other typefaces including [[Myriad (typeface)|Myriad]] and [[Univers]], calling it "a Four-headed Frankenfont".<ref name="Frankenfont" />
